HashingVectorizer is an NLP technique that converts text into numbers using a hash function instead of storing a vocabulary dictionary.

Simple Definition

HashingVectorizer converts text into numerical vectors by mapping words to fixed columns using mathematical hashing.

========


Real-Time Example

Review

This movie is amazing
CountVectorizer

Creates a vocabulary:

| Word    | Index |
| ------- | ----- |
| this    | 0     |
| movie   | 1     |
| amazing | 2     |

Output:

[1,1,1]

It stores the vocabulary.

===============

HashingVectorizer

Does NOT create a vocabulary.

Instead:

this    → column 15
movie   → column 120
amazing → column 78

Output:

[0,0,0,1,0,0,1,...]

Words are placed into columns using a hash formula.

===============

Work Flow

| Step | Process                       |
| ---- | ----------------------------- |
| 1    | Input Text                    |
| 2    | Hash Function Applied         |
| 3    | Words Mapped to Fixed Columns |
| 4    | Numerical Vector Created      |
| 5    | Sent to ML Model              |

