CountVectorizer vs TF-IDF vs HashingVectorizer
----------------------------------------------


| Feature                 | CountVectorizer | TF-IDF | HashingVectorizer |
| ----------------------- | --------------- | ------ | ----------------- |
| Counts Words            | ✅               | ✅      | ✅                 |
| Stores Vocabulary       | ✅               | ✅      | ❌                 |
| Memory Usage            | High            | Medium | Low               |
| Speed                   | Medium          | Medium | Fast              |
| Suitable for Large Data | ❌               | ❌      | ✅                 |
| Interpretable Features  | ✅               | ✅      | ❌                 |

==================

Why Use HashingVectorizer?

Suppose:

Dataset = 10 Million Tweets

CountVectorizer:

Vocabulary = 500,000 words
Memory = Very High

HashingVectorizer:

No Vocabulary Storage
Memory = Low
Processing = Faster

That's why it's used for large-scale NLP systems.

